==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ethyl alcohol
<hw>ethyl alcohol</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>the organic
compound <chform>C2H5.OH</chform>, which is the intoxicating agent in
beer, wine, and other fermented and distilled liquors; it is used pure
or denatured as a solvent or in medicines and colognes and cleaning
solutions and rocket fuel.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ethanol, fermentation alcohol, grain
alcohol.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethylamine</ent>⟦br⟧
